<TITLE> 16 killed in Faridpur road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com)  At least 16 people were killed and 40 injured as two buses hit in Bhanga upazila, Faridpur, on Sunday, an official said. Shafikul Islam, Upazila Nirbahi Officer, told bdnews24.com: "We heard ten people died on the spot when a bus crashed head-on with another on the Dhaka-Barisal highway at Koidubi Sadardi area at around 4.45pm." "We have since heard six more died at the scene. At least 40 passengers of both buses were injured," he said. The injured were taken to nearby hospitals, he said, but could not give further details. The deceased could not be identified immediately, Islam said. bdnews24
